main event: An unidentified object, possibly a stone, was observed at Frenchman's Bayou, Arkansas on 21 May 1958.
interesting points: The object was found in gumbo type soil and measured approximately 10 pounds., It was determined to be nonmagnetic before disposal., There were multiple hypotheses regarding the nature of the object including balloon, aircraft, and astronomical origins., The field where the object was found is not known for such rocks or metals., The object was forwarded for evaluation due to its potential extraterrestrial origin.
sighted object: rock or stone similar in appearance to a meteorite
witness description: Mr. representative owner of the field where the object was found
